# Testing Rules

## General
- Write tests for critical business logic and complex functions.
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior:
```typescript
it("should show error message when email is invalid", () => { ... })
```
- Follow the AAA pattern: Arrange → Act → Assert.
- Each test should test one thing only.

## Tools
- Unit tests: Vitest or Jest
- Component tests: React Testing Library
- E2E tests: Playwright (when needed)

## What to Test
- Form validation logic
- Custom hooks with complex logic
- Utility/helper functions
- API service functions (mock the HTTP layer)
- User interactions in critical flows (login, checkout, etc.)

## What NOT to Test
- shadcn/ui components (they're already tested)
- Simple presentational components with no logic
- CSS/styling
- Third-party library internals
